                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18160110-31-off171 t18160110-31-crimeloc174"></join>. Between three and four o'clock in the afternoon of the 20th of December, I was in a shop of ours, which is opposite to the one from which the desk in question was stolen. I observed the prisoner, in company with another man, and rather suspected them. The prisoner opened the shop door, and went in, and brought out this desk.I immediately crossed over, and stopped him with it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I shewed the gentleman the person that sent me in for the desk; it was the man that was in company with me.</p>
               <p>(Property produced, and sworn to.)</p>
